      <title>1841 Mar. 24, Carthage, Tennessee [to unknown recipient] / [Adam Fergusson]</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This is a letter to an unknown recipient dated March 24, 1841. The author is probably Adam Fergusson. The letter is to an agent involved with treaties with Native nations. Fergusson is trying to find information on Mary Jameson, an American who, as a child was taken captive by a Seneca tribe in New York state. He wants to find out if she has any living descendants in order to ascertain whether her two brothers in Tennessee are her legal heirs. This is in relation to land given by the Seneca Nation in a treaty with the United States.</abstract>
